news.title: Gurugram: Mahira Infratech assures delivery, but buyers worry about delay
news.para: Homebuyers of Mahira Homes fear an inordinate delay in getting possession of their flats, with the department of town and country planning (DTCP) and the developer making different claims about the completion of the affordable housing project in Sector 68.

news.title: Bhopal: Realtor sentenced to life for duping 250 people
news.para: A lookout notice was issued for him after he went missing and he was arrested from Indore airport while he was trying to escape abroad. The court also slapped a fine of Rs 20,000 on the accused.

news.title: ED starts process to sell off Nirav Modi's Mumbai homes
news.para: The ED and income-tax authority had earlier recovered around Rs 130 crore after auctioning Modi's luxury, fashion and art items, mostly paintings, vehicles, and watches.

news.title: HDFC Bank leases 2.5 lakh sq ft office space in Mindspace REIT's business park
news.para: The office tower, which is part of Mindspace business park’s first phase, is currently under development and is expected to be completed in the next 3-4 months when the bank will start its fit-out work.

news.title: Adjudicating or appellate authority can't sit in appeal over commercial wisdom of CoC: SC
news.para: The apex court observed that interference would be warranted only when the National Company Law Tribunal (NCLT) or the National Company Law Appellate Tribunal (NCLAT) finds the decision of CoC to be "wholly capricious" and arbitrary.

news.title: Uphaar fire: Ansal brothers tampering with evidence eroded judicial integrity, court told
news.para: ​The prosecution submitted to District Judge Dharmesh Sharma while opposing a plea filed by the Ansal brothers challenging their conviction and the 7-year jail terms by a magisterial court in November last year.

news.title: Sebi allows virtual annual meetings for InvITs, REITs till end of December
news.para: ​The circular came after Sebi received representations from REITs/InvITs to further extend the facility to conduct annual meetings and other meetings of unitholders through Video-Conferencing (VC) or through Other Audio-Visual Means (OAVM).

news.title: Tata Projects to develop Noida International Airport
news.para: The company has been selected from three shortlisted teams and will construct the terminal, runway, airside infrastructure, roads, utilities, landside facilities and other ancillary buildings at the airport.

news.title: Chennai metro work on IT corridor to begin soon
news.para: ​Chennai Metro Rail Limited (CMRL) recently awarded the contract to Larsen & Toubro to construct the elevated section with 10 stations within a period of 36 months.

news.title: The incorporation of sustainable energy in real estate
news.para: The real estate industry accounts for almost 36% of total energy use and 39% of energy and process-related carbon dioxide (CO2) emissions, with 11% of those emissions coming from the manufacturing of building materials and products such as steel, cement, and glass.

news.title: Unsold housing stock rise marginally across top eight cities in Jan-March quarter: Report
news.para: As per the data, the unsold inventories increased to 9,01,967 units during January-March period of this year from 8,94,100 units in the previous quarter.

news.title: Gujarat: Junagadh and Jamnagar chosen for global climate change projects
news.para: GCoM is the largest global alliance for city climate leadership working with cities and local governments. A GCoM team visited the two cities in the last two days.

news.title: Bengaluru: BDA promises infra at the earliest in Nadaprabhu Kempegowda Layout
news.para: Members of the legislature petition committee (LPC) on Thursday reviewed ongoing infrastructure works at the layout where the site allottees have been denied basic facilities even years after allotments.

news.title: HC extends stay on demolition of two colonies in Chandigarh
news.para: ​The case will now come up for hearing in September. During resumed hearing on Wednesday, the court asked the Centre to explore ways to rehabilitate slum dwellers on the same land.

news.title: Register property at any sub registrar's office in Bengaluru
news.para: Revenue minister R Ashoka said the government is planning to introduce the concept on a pilot basis in Bengaluru soon. He said besides easing registration hassles for people, it will help get rid of middlemen, touts, and corruption within sub-registrar offices.
